crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a legitimate Windows kernel-mode driver, identified as a component of a security software suite (NSecsoft) by its PDB path and internal strings. It implements standard endpoint protection features, including process monitoring via PsSetCreateProcessNotifyRoutine, image load tracking via PsSetLoadImageNotifyRoutine, and process handle filtering using ObRegisterCallbacks to prevent unauthorized process termination. It also exposes a kernel-level process termination primitive through IOCTL 0x2248e0, allowing the associated user-mode application to kill processes from kernel space. Relevant IOCs include the symbolic link '\DosDevices\NSecKrnl' and the PDB path 'D:\NSecsoft\NSec\NSEC-Client-Kernel\Drivers\NSecKrnl\NSecKrnl\bin\NSecKrnl64.pdb'.
